{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"679790d4-5b2d-4922-85aa-56de5c6c7af6","content":"Two things changed with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax changed\nMTP doesn't use VSTest's `--filter`. The new CLI flag is `--filter` but with **different syntax**. The `&` operator becomes `/` and `~` (contains) becomes `~=`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~=IntegrationTests/Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n| VSTest | MTP |\n|---|---|\n| `~` (contains) | `~=` |\n| `=` (equals) | `=` |\n| `&` (and) | `/` |\n| `\\|` (or) | `\\|` |\n\n### 2. `[Trait]` → `[Category]` for Category filters\nxUnit v3 replaces `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` with the first-class `[Category]` attribute (from `Xunit.v3`). Update your test:\n\n```csharp\n[Category(\"Smoke\")]   // was: [Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]\npublic class IntegrationTests\n```\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes to your files?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"333d2cf3-1362-4b92-92b8-621d02689a4a","outputTokens":284,"requestId":"042B:29B12:1F8F623:236D494:69E81BD4"},"id":"ed0b13e8-f7b7-4415-ab69-0e32c1e6ac44","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:52:43.136Z","parentId":"4965dd7b-6585-4c02-9d4b-1cb015f66cdd"}
